content.description: Easy jugging and stemming in a cozy chimney to get to the "Sun Deck." Careful - the final holds to top out are polished. Find a great belay stance beyond the first set of chains to belay your follower.
content.protection: Bolts, multiple lower offs on the top.
content.location: The obvious on the right side of the lower ledges at Fun Rock.

content.description: A thin face that slowly progresses to vertical. No obvious crux.
content.protection: Bolts with chain anchors. There is also a belay bolt (shared with Plethora).
content.location: Just to the right of Plethora. The route starts from a ledge with a drop off to your left.

content.description: Starts on the first few bolts of Cream (5.7), then heads directly up over the bulge. Crank a few moves on good holds (but bad feet) to clear the bulge. A few thin moves to the chains.
content.location: Start as for Cream, the right-most climb on Fun Rock proper (but below Sunbug Slab).

content.description: Short fun climb turning two roofs.
content.location: At the trailboard look at the wall and you'll see it to the left of a chimney.

content.description: This is a cool route with some nice sequences.  The start is thin and technical, but the crux (especially for shorter folks) is up higher in the crack.
content.protection: This was at one time a trad climb with one bolt protecting the face at the bottom.  It has since been fully retro-bolted, and can be led on a handful of quickdraws.  To lead it traditionally, bring gear to 2" with an emphasis in the small stuff (i.e. Aliens).  There is a 3-bolt anchor on top equipped with chains for rappelling.
content.location:
On the main wall of Fun Rock, toward the left-hand side.  There are two bolted cracks, this is the one on the left.  The other is

Kids Nowadays

and is rated .10d or .11a.

content.description:
Short, simple sport climb with plenty of easy holds. Great for a warmup or a first lead, first bolt is not too strung out.

Note: This route is not listed in the Burdo guidebook.
content.location: To the right of Bolterheist, furthest right bolted route on the Sunbug Slab.

content.description: A short route that offers access to the anchors above the overhang by skirting the face to the left and climbing the slab.
content.location: Same start as Magic Limbo Cha-Cha.

content.description: Low-angle moves on good edges bring you to an overhanging bulge crux.  Pull this and head up to a wide seam, clipping a bolt to your left and heading up the gap for another move or so before traversing out onto the upper face.  Follow easier terrain up and left to the anchors.
content.location: Immediately right of "Finger Food" 10b.Â  On the Sunbug Slab.

content.description: The route is a thin face that is less than vertical.  It is very sustained for the majority of the route with no obvious crux.  There are a few runout sections as the route eases near the top.
content.protection: 10 Bolts with chain anchors. There is also a belay bolt.
content.location: The route is located in the middle of Fun Rock.  Just to the left of Two Bolts or Not.  The route starts off a ledge with a dropoff to your left.

content.description: Great route to try first outdoor lead. A nice staircase of holds.
content.location: Farthest right (uphill) route.

content.description: Ascend the broken crack system, staying right to avoid the 5.10 head-wall of "Crutch".
content.protection: 9 bolts to chains at the top
content.location: Start is to the right of the crack system.

content.description:
This is a beautiful long route that starts on a steep thin face, moves through a slab, then onto a great arete.

Two distinct cruxes: one low, and one high.  The rest of the climbing is in the 5.7/5.8 range.
content.location:
WARNING:

This route is

long

.  Lowering with a 60m rope will not quite get you to the ground, but it will get you close enough to downclimb if you clean the draws off the middle part of the route.  Please be sure to tie a knot in the end of your rope.  Alternatively, there is a 2-bolt anchor at the top of the 5.11 to the right of this route.  This anchor is below the anchor for

Megafauna

.

The start of this climb is the thin face immediately to the right of the

Invasive Species

crack, and climbs up into the thin finger crack next to that route.  Look for the big arete up high (which can alternatively be chimneyed through easily enough).

Megafauna

crosses

Cream

, and may share a bolt (depending on if you clip it not).

content.description: Climb the face to the left side of the overhang, traverse out right to the second overhang, and then straight up to the anchor.
content.location: To the left of Steppenruf.

content.description: This route is short and sweet. It has a bouldery start. Then some thin climbing with some tough moves, to an optional 4th bolt on easy slab, or left to the walk out up to the anchors. The climb uses the intermediate anchors on drive-by-nose-job. To the left, between Left hand Man and Arapilesian Dog there are a couple easy bolt lines which allow access to the anchors as well for top roping.
content.location: At end of walk into main wall, just before you turn left. Around the corner from Magic Limbo Cha-Cha

content.description:
Fun thin climbing that rewards good footwork - one of the better routes at the crag.

Easy climbing to a horizontal break gets you to the first bolt. Then follow an obvious "crack" system through a thin crux into solid finger locks. After the last bolt there's a bit of space before the anchor through easy terrain. Continue up for 2 optional extensions - the left option is 5.9 and the right option is 5.10a.
content.protection: 6 bolts. Anchor with steel lower-off biners is shared with Invasive Species.
content.location: The left and more thin of the two cracks on the right of Snakefingers. The right crack is Invasive Species.

content.description:
Hand and finger crack just left of

Megafauna 5.9

.  This climb has great pro placements and is a lot of fun.  The only downside is how short it is.
content.protection:
bolts now.  Can also TR by climbing

Cream

, 5.7.

content.description: Although short, the route is certainly a standout of the Mazama climbs, especially if you like thin face climbing.  The meat of the route is navigating the barer looking face through the final three bolts.
content.protection: 5 Bolts to the Chains situated to the right.
content.location: Near the bottom of Fun Rock, Guide's Day sits on the face to the left of the broken crack of Snakefingers.

content.description: Pulling the bulge with thin holds makes the crux, finish is runout but easy.
content.location: 50ft or so up the hill from the trailboard. Bolts lead through an obvious bulge about halfway up the route.

content.description: This face just right of the 'fault line'. Â Finish on "Crutch" head-wall.
content.location: Start is left of Psychological Crutch.

content.description: Climb the face/arete right of the chimney and continue up the arete.
Crux is pulling the first roof
content.location: Same start as Magic Limbo Cha-Cha, but go right to pull the first roof.

content.description:
A leftward diagonal climb on the slab at the far right of Fun Rock before the Sunbug Slab.  Start at a thin face, climbing through cool moves for the grade.  This climb diagonals left past

Megafauna 5.9

, to an anchor above

Invasive Species 5.8

and

Kids Nowadays 5.11a

, allowing a top-rope on all three of these fine climbs.

Three more bolts continue above the anchors at 5.9 to a second set of chains (at 80').
content.protection: 5 bolts (or 8 bolts for the 5.9 full-value variation), plus chains.
content.location:
Just left of

Megafauna

.  The first two bolts of this route also provide the start for the steep

Swell 5.11a

.

content.description: Same start as Wide Load. After the first bulge move left onto the face adjacent to Steppenruf.
content.location: Same start as "Wide Load" in the chimney to the left of "Drive By Nose Job"

content.description: Straightforward sport route with lots of options to get up the face. Stay left of the bolts for the best climbing. Right of the bolts feels more like a 5.4.
content.location: There is a fissure on the right end of Sunbug slab with bolted lines on either side of it. This climb, to the right of that fissure, is the more easy of these two easy clip-ups (the other climb is Boltergeist, 5.8).

content.description: Trends slightly right as it heads up Sunbug Slab on positive holds.

Arapilesian Dog is a cool route with solid rock and fun moves.  The crux comes high moving around the corner near the final bolt.  Lower down the climbing is not as steep but there is a hard spot that is made easier by stemming onto the boulder out left.  One of the best routes I got on at Mazama.
content.location: Just to the left of the Sun Deck area on Fun Rock is an orange and white streaked rock that is overhanging.  Arapilesian Dog is on this and climbs up and out left of the overhang.

content.description: Shares start with Gridlock, then breaks left following the bolt line 2/3rds up the wall. The rock gets much more interesting and entertaining in the blocky terrain on the upper portion of this route.
content.protection: bolts, steel carabiners at the anchors (as of August 2017)
content.location: Third route from the left on the upper section of the wall
